	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>1210 Napau Street New York</placeName></p>
				<p rend="align(right)"><date>17<hi rend="sup">th</hi>. Sepr. 1850</date></p>
				<p>The <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(4)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">&#47;The copy of the Occident usually sent to<lb/> the Office of the Asmonean has not been received for the<lb/> current month&#44; but my attention has been called to an<lb/> editorial article therein&#44; entitled&#44; &#8220;<persName>Dr. Wise</persName> and his<lb/> congregation&#8221; in which appears the following observations&#58;</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">&#8220;They communicate to us certain doings of the editor<lb/> of the latter paper&#44; which we do not choose to<lb/> publish&#44; as we mean not to interfere with our<lb/> <sic>cotemporary</sic>&#44; for we should at once be taxed<lb/> with wishing to injure him&#44; for the sake of<lb/> increasing our circulation&#44; a charge which<lb/> we do not <add>care</add> just now to bring down on us.  But<lb/> the acts of baseness &#40;which if true&#44; ought to cover<lb/> the perpetrators with everlasting infamy&#47;alleged<lb/> to have been committed against <persName>Dr. Wise</persName>&#44; do not<lb/> unfortunately contradict the statement which we<lb/> said before the public.&#8221;</p>
				<p>The inference which has been drawn from the above quoted<lb/> sentences&#44; necessitates me to request that you will&#44; at</p>
				<p rend="The following is written in the top left corner of the page.">Editor of<lb/> Asmonean<lb/> Re&#58; <persName>Wise</persName>&#8212;</p>
			<pb n="1V"/>
				<p>your earliest convenience&#44; favor me with a statement<lb/> of the &#8220;certain doings of the Editor of the Asmonean&#8221; which<lb/> have been communicated to you&#44; and that you will further<lb/> please to state&#44; if you apply the term &#8220;acts of baseness&#8221; to<lb/> any conduct of mine</p>
			<p rend="indent(7)">I am dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)">Yours respectfully</p>
			<p rend="indent(9)"><hi rend="underline"><persName role="author">Rob Lyons</persName></hi></p>
			
